<p>“I&#8217;ve enjoyed Jinwoo Chong&#8217;s short fiction and was thrilled to see this novel, a portrait of family members trying hard to reconnect with each other—it is wryly funny and unexpectedly heartwarming and (dare I say) expands the conception of what Asian American literature gets to be.”</p>
