<p>“We could fill many books with everything JD Vance wilfully misunderstands about reproductive justice; two novels that get it right include Sayaka Murata&#8217;s bonkers <i>Vanishing World</i>, a speculative fiction masterpiece that lampoons demographic panic, and Hilary Plum&#8217;s <i>State Champ</i>, a darkly funny Clarice Lispectorian tale of an abortion rights protestor.”</p>
